# Biome Key Rules

## Configuration
- Single shared config with full recommended rules (strict TS/JSX); no overrides.
- Version-control config; document exceptions inline.
- Exclude test files and generated files in biome.json configuration.

## Usage
- Run `biome check --write` in CI/pre-commit; fail on unused symbols, syntax, violations.
- Let Biome handle imports, commas, semicolons, whitespace.

## Integration
- IDE on-save feedback; CI before tests.
- Ignore only generated/vendored; curate list.
- Configure files.exclude in biome.json: test files, generated files, build outputs.

## Avoid
- Manual post-Biome formatting.
- Disabling rules without fixes.
- Shipping unused imports/unreachable code.
